                            <comment id="17063913" author="tison" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 13:39:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems the problem is that we want to support &lt;tt&gt;executeAsync&lt;/tt&gt; while keep &lt;tt&gt;JobClient&lt;/tt&gt; &quot;stateless&quot; so that we don&apos;t have to manage resource. Thus, we add a terminate future in &lt;tt&gt;LocalExecutor&lt;/tt&gt; to terminate the cluster when the job finished, which, as described here, possibly race with a separated result request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My opinion would be still we(and the user) manage &lt;tt&gt;JobClient&lt;/tt&gt; lifecycle so that we ensure the result delivered in &lt;tt&gt;execute&lt;/tt&gt; (blocking version). Alternative is we make something like &lt;tt&gt;MiniDispatcher&lt;/tt&gt; to special handle it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think? cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kkl0u&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kkl0u&quot;&gt;kkl0u&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aljoscha&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aljoscha&quot;&gt;aljoscha&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17063916" author="tison" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 13:45:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ref&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/c927e176f35b9db0f9daec7b67ccdb41d8e7d9f5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/c927e176f35b9db0f9daec7b67ccdb41d8e7d9f5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/41176ba0189ef2782449a1b7d4d074adc8a4af6f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/41176ba0189ef2782449a1b7d4d074adc8a4af6f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17063927" author="mxm" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 14:35:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tison&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tison&quot;&gt;tison&lt;/a&gt;. Not sure if you saw the PR already. I&apos;ve opened it shortly after opening this issue. I went for a per-job mini cluster client which handles the shutdown and caches the result. This seemed like the best solution to me and avoids altering any of the JobClient logic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17063928" author="tison" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 14:37:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mxm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mxm&quot;&gt;mxm&lt;/a&gt;! Yes I checked the PR. It is the case where I mentioned as &quot;special handling&quot;. And it should work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
